message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The patient is most likely suffering from polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS), which is characterized by irregular periods, elevated androgens, and obesity. Without treatment, she is at greatest risk for developing endometrial carcinoma due to prolonged exposure to unopposed estrogen. Cervical carcinoma and choriocarcinoma are not related to PCOS, and mature cystic teratoma is a benign ovarian tumor.
